cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a novel system for unsupervised action recognition based on body keypoints sequences. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves processing visual data. The system is based on a recurrent neural network, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions that the encoder learns a separable feature representation, which suggests the use of neural networks for feature extraction (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the system on action recognition benchmarks, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
